laboratory_examinations.findings: Liver demonstrates diffuse hypoattenuation, consistent with mild hepatic steatosis. No evidence of focal lesions.
Hyperemic, enlarged appendix measuring up to 12 mm with surrounding fat stranding, consistent with appendicitis. There is a 4 mm appendicolith seen at the appendix base. No free air, no free fluid.
Creatinine level is 2.1 mg/dL, which is outside the normal range (2.7 - 4.5 mg/dL).
